He's no stranger to making waves, so perhaps AKA was always destined to be on radio. The hip hop artist, real name Kiernan Forbes, has reportedly landed himself a radio slot on Touch HD. The Super Mega Show is slated for broadcast on June 19 and, according to Touch HD manager Martin Vilikazi, will be "an innovative programme that will blow people away". In December, AKA announced that he would be leaving his record label Vth in order to establish his own company. Recently, he confirmed that all aspects of their business relationship had concluded. 